{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01BaFsx7CP7giX8aRKrAfxjG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me plan this carefully. I need to generate 10 fake OCR recipe text files with specific requirements:\n\n1. **File locations**: `tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.21.txt`\n2. **Filename rules**: \n   - Use SPACES, not hyphens\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics\n   - Filename title must match text content title\n3. **Recipe mix**: ~60% English, ~40% Polish\n4. **Pattern breakdown**:\n   - 4 files with SPLIT_TITLE\n   - 4 files with METADATA_PREFIX\n   - 2 files with OCR_CORRUPTION\n5. **File length**: 15-60 lines, spillover files 40-60 lines\n6. **Exclude existing recipes** - I have a long list to avoid\n\nLet me generate 10 different recipes:\n\n**English recipes (6):**\n1. Mushroom Soup with Thyme - METADATA_PREFIX\n2. Lemon Cheesecake - SPLIT_TITLE\n3. Crispy Eggplant - OCR_CORRUPTION\n4. Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli - METADATA_PREFIX\n5. Chocolate Chip Brownies - SPLIT_TITLE\n6. Grilled Trout with Herbs - METADATA_PREFIX\n\n**Polish recipes (4):**\n1. Zupa Cebulowa - SPLIT_TITLE\n2. Placki Ziemniaczane - OCR_CORRUPTION\n3. Pierniki Miodowe - METADATA_PREFIX\n4. Barszcz Ukraiński - SPLIT_TITLE\n\nLet me make sure these are all different from the excluded list. Looking through the excluded list, I don't see any of these exact titles, so I'm good.\n\nNow let me create them with the proper patterns:\n\n**Pattern Distribution:**\n1. Mushroom Soup with Thyme - METADATA_PREFIX (English)\n\n\n2. Zupa Cebulowa - SPLIT_TITLE (Polish)\n3. Crispy Eggplant - OCR_CORRUPTION (English)\n4. Placki Ziemniaczane - OCR_CORRUPTION (Polish)\n5. Lemon Cheesecake - SPLIT_TITLE (English)\n6. Pierniki Miodowe - METADATA_PREFIX (Polish)\n7. Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli - METADATA_PREFIX (English)\n8. Barszcz Ukraiński - SPLIT_TITLE (Polish)\n9. Chocolate Chip Brownies - SPLIT_TITLE (English)\n10. Grilled Trout with Herbs - METADATA_PREFIX (English)\n\nNow I'll create each file with the appropriate pattern and content structure. I, thyme, salt, and pepper to taste\n\nFor the SPLIT_TITLE entries, I'm breaking titles into fragments across lines. For METADATA_PREFIX entries, I'm prepending category and timing information before the actual title. For OCR_CORRUPTION entries, I'm introducing character substitutions—swapping accented characters for numbers, using similar-looking letters, adding hyphenation artifacts and random tokens to simulate scanning errors. Zupa cebulowa wymaga kilogramów cebuli, masła, bulionu mięsnego i białego wina. Cebulę kroi się na cienkie plasterki, następnie przesmażuje na wolnym ogniu przez 30 minut aż nabierze złotego koloru. Po dodaniu wina gotuje się przez 5 minut, wlewa bulion i gotuje kolejne 20 minut, na koniec doprawiając solą i pieprzem. ish with fresh basil and serve.\n\nThe preparation involves coating eggplant slices with flour, egg, and breadcrumbs before frying until golden. Once fried, the slices are topped with mozzarella and tomato sauce, then baked until the cheese melts. A garnish of fresh basil completes the dish. Grate the potatoes and onions on a fine grater, then squeeze out excess liquid. Mix in eggs, flour, and salt to form a batter. Heat oil in a pan over high heat, shape the mixture into patties, and fry until golden on both sides. Serve with sour cream or applesauce.\n\nFor the cheesecake, combine crushed digestive biscuits with melted butter and press into a springform pan. Beat softened cream cheese with sugar until smooth, then incorporate eggs one at a time. Fold in sour cream along with lemon zest and juice, pour the filling over the crust, and bake at 160°C for 45-50 minutes until the center sets. Allow to cool completely before serving.\n\nFor honey gingerbread cookies, you'll need flour, honey, butter, eggs, pepper, anise, baking soda, salt, and powdered sugar for dusting. The preparation takes about 20 minutes with 25 minutes of baking time, yielding roughly 30 pieces.\n\nStart by melting the honey and butter together over low heat, then cool slightly before incorporating the eggs. Mix the flour with the honey-butter-egg mixture, add the spices and baking soda, and knead for 5 minutes. Refrigerate the dough for 30 minutes, then roll it out to 5mm thickness and cut into cookie shapes. Bake at 180°C for 25 minutes and finish with a dusting of powdered sugar.\n\nFor the pasta dough, combine 400g flour with 4 eggs, salt, and olive oil, kneading until the texture becomes smooth. Let it rest wrapped in plastic for half an hour. The filling requires wilted spinach mixed with ricotta and Parmesan cheese, an egg, nutmeg, salt, pepper, and optional pine nuts. The sauce comes together with butter and sage leaves warmed through with seasoning.\n\nRoll out the dough thinly on a floured surface and cut into circles. Fill each one, fold, and seal the edges carefully. Boil salted water in a pot, then add the ravioli and cook until they rise to the surface, followed by another 2 minutes. Finish by tossing with the butter and sage mixture, then plate and serve right away.\n\nFor the barszcz, peel and julienne the beets and carrots, then cube the potatoes and halve the onion. Add all vegetables to a pot with water and bay leaves, simmering for 45 minutes until tender. Season with vinegar, salt, and pepper, then serve topped with sour cream.\n\nNow for the brownies: preheat the oven to 180°C and melt butter with chopped dark chocolate over low heat. Mix in sugar followed by eggs one at a time, then vanilla extract. Combine flour, cocoa powder, and salt in a separate bowl, then fold into the chocolate mixture along with chocolate chips before baking.\n\nFor the grilled trout recipe, it's a quick summer dish that serves four people. You'll need whole cleaned trout, olive oil, and fresh herbs like dill, parsley, and thyme to season the fish before grilling.\n\nThe method involves prepping the trout by patting them dry and scoring the skin, then stuffing the cavities with the herb mixture and lemon slices. After brushing with oil and seasoning, they go on the grill for about 8-10 minutes per side until cooked through, finishing with fresh lemon halves on the side.\n\nNow I need to create 10 separate Write calls to save each file.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":65361,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":65361},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c8cca03-ebc9-4385-bb87-ac76765b8d75","uuid":"02d64aec-8f33-42bc-b83a-0179f7f7e8cf"}
